{"word":"ἔχιδνα","slug":"ἔχιδνα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔχιδνα</b></el> <el>(ἔχιδνα, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔχις'><el>ἔχις</el></a>\n<p/><i>an adder, viper</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of a treacherous wife or friend, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}